data.content:
Gdańsk University of Technology
Here is the comprehensive description:

Gdańsk University of Technology is a Polish university that provides education and conducts research. It offers bachelor's and master's degree studies. As an educational institution, it defines and has its own rules and regulations for students. Additionally, it has its own portal, regulations, and procedures, as well as a student government, which ensures that students have a say in the decision-making process.

individual student
An individual student is a learner who has an individual account in the 'Moja PG' system and is pursuing a course of studies.

Moja PG
'Moja PG' is an electronic system that contains information on a student's studies and current status.<SEP>Moja PG is a portal where students can access information and register for classes.<SEP>Moja PG is an electronic system for students to access information and submit applications.

academic teacher
An academic teacher is responsible for teaching and awarding grades to students in a particular subject.

Gdańsk
"Gdańsk is a city where Gdańsk University of Technology is located.<SEP>Gdańsk is a city in Poland and the location of Gdańsk University of Technology.<SEP>Gdańsk is a location where Gdańsk University of Technology is situated.<SEP>Gdańsk is a location where the university is situated.<SEP>Gdańsk is the location of the University of Technology.

thesis supervisor
A thesis supervisor is an academic teacher or a person from outside Gdańsk University of Technology responsible for supporting the student in the course of work related to the preparation of the thesis.<SEP>A thesis supervisor is an academic teacher or an outside person responsible for guiding a student in the preparation of a diploma thesis.

ECTS credits
ECTS credits are a measure of the average workload of a student, necessary to obtain particular learning outcomes.

learning outcomes
Learning outcomes are the amount of knowledge, competence, and social skills acquired as a result of the educational process.

credit point deficit
A credit point deficit is the total number of ECTS credits for failed subjects in all semesters.

individual student account
An individual student account is an account in the University electronic system 'Moja PG', containing information on the student's course of studies and current status.

individual research studies
Individual research studies are individual studies for the most talented master's degree students involving the implementation of scientific research as part of research projects.

individual inter-disciplinary studies
Individual inter-disciplinary studies are individual research studies, the program of which includes at least two fields and allows for obtaining a diploma in more than one field of study.

course
A course is a programme in a field of study, pursued by students commencing studies in a particular academic year.

module
A module is a subject or a group of subjects.

data.entity_name: academic teacher responsible for the subject
data.content:
academic teacher responsible for the subject
An academic teacher responsible for the subject is an academic teacher who is responsible for proper realization of the subject by all academic teachers conducting classes as part of the subject, and awards final grades to students attending the classes.

academic teacher conducting classes
An academic teacher conducting classes is an academic teacher conducting a given type of class as part of the subject.

study plan
A study plan is a schedule for subjects included in a curriculum.

data.entity_name: repeating classes in a failed subject
data.content:
repeating classes in a failed subject
Repeating classes in a failed subject is attending a class again and retaking a credit or examination in a previously failed subject.

diploma thesis
A diploma thesis is a research project that a student must complete to obtain a degree.

study program
A study program is learning outcomes and a description of the learning process leading to learning outcomes with ECTS credits assigned to individual modules of the process.

subject
A subject is a unit of learning including classes or groups of classes, to which specific learning outcomes and a number of ECTS credits have been ascribed.

restoration of student rights
Restoration of student rights concerns the possibility of returning to study for students previously deleted from the student register.

semester
A semester is a period of study.

year of study
A year of study is two consecutive semesters of study.

Student
A student is an individual who attends classes and participates in studies at Gdańsk University of Technology.<SEP>Students are individuals enrolled in academic programs at Gdańsk University of Technology.<SEP>Students are individuals who have rights and obligations within the university.

Rector
The Rector is responsible for providing regulations and guidelines for students.<SEP>The rector is a person authorized to make decisions and approvals related to studies at Gdańsk University of Technology.

Semester
A Semester is a period of time that comprises part of the Academic Year, divided into winter and summer.<SEP>A semester is a period of study at Gdańsk University of Technology, which lasts several months.<SEP>Semester is a duration of the academic cycle at Gdańsk University of Technology.<SEP>Semester is a period of time during which classes are held.<SEP>Semesters are periods of academic study, typically lasting several months.

The Senate of Gdańsk University of Technology is a governing body that determines the conditions and procedures for recruitment and studies.

Recruitment Procedure

Transfer from Another University

Confirmation of Learning Outcomes
Confirmation of learning outcomes is a process of recognizing and validating student's academic achievements.

Learning Outcomes

University Student Account

Moja PG System
Moja PG system is an electronic system used by students at Gdańsk University of Technology for various purposes.<SEP>The Moja PG System is an online platform used by students and academic teachers to manage studies and access information.

Health and Safety Training
Health and safety training is a mandatory training program for students at Gdańsk University of Technology.

Library Training
Library training is a mandatory training program for students at Gdańsk University of Technology.

Moja PG System Training
Moja PG system training is a mandatory training program for students at Gdańsk University of Technology.

data.entity_name: Student Government of Gdańsk University of Technology
data.content:
Student Government of Gdańsk University of Technology
The Student Government of Gdańsk University of Technology is a student organization that cooperates with the Students’ Parliament of the Republic of Poland.<SEP>The Student Government of Gdańsk University of Technology is responsible for governing student affairs and has its own regulations.

data.entity_name: Students Parliament of the Republic of Poland
data.content:
Students Parliament of the Republic of Poland
The Students’ Parliament of the Republic of Poland is a national student organization that cooperates with student governments of individual universities.

data.entity_name: Rector of Gdańsk University of Technology
data.content:
Rector of Gdańsk University of Technology
The Rector of Gdańsk University of Technology is the superior of all university students and responsible for decision-making.

data.entity_name: Dean of a Faculty of Gdańsk University of Technology
data.content:
Dean of a Faculty of Gdańsk University of Technology
The Dean of a Faculty of Gdańsk University of Technology is the superior of all students at a given faculty and responsible for faculty-specific decisions.

Academic Year
The Academic Year is a period of time that starts on 1 October and ends on 30 September, comprising two semesters: winter and summer.

Studies
Studies refer to the educational programs and activities conducted at Gdańsk University of Technology.

ECTS Catalog
The ECTS Catalog is a collection of study programs and courses offered by Gdańsk University of Technology.

Faculty
A Faculty is a division of Gdańsk University of Technology responsible for a specific field of study.<SEP>The Faculty is the head of a department at Gdańsk University of Technology.<SEP>The faculty is a department within Gdańsk University of Technology, responsible for academic programs.

Winter Semester
The Winter Semester is a period of time that starts in October and ends in February, comprising part of the Academic Year.

Summer Semester
The Summer Semester is a period of time that starts in March and ends in September, comprising part of the Academic Year.

Examination Session
An Examination Session is a time when students take exams to demonstrate their knowledge and skills.

Internship
An Internship is a period of time when students gain practical experience in a specific industry or organization.

Holiday
A Holiday is a period of time when students are not obligated to attend classes.

Gdańsk Tech Student Government
Gdańsk Tech Student Government is the student government that represents students' interests and has its own regulations.

Faculty Student Council
The Faculty Student Council is the main representative body of students at a given faculty and works to support their interests and initiate activities aimed at improving studying conditions.

starosta
A starosta is a representative of a student group and is elected according to the regulations of the Gdańsk Tech Student Government.

Dean
The Dean is a high-ranking official responsible for overseeing the academic affairs of a faculty.<SEP>The Dean is a person with decision-making authority in academic matters at Gdańsk University of Technology<SEP>The Dean is responsible for overseeing the academic activities of the students.

Academic Teacher
An Academic Teacher is a professor who conducts classes and consults with students.

Student Group
Student Group is a unit of students at Gdańsk University of Technology.

President/Starosta of the Group
The President/Starosta of the Group is the representative of the student group.

data.entity_name: Faculty Representative of the Gdańsk Tech Student Government
data.content:
Faculty Representative of the Gdańsk Tech Student Government
The Faculty Representative of the Gdańsk Tech Student Government is the liaison between the student government and the faculty.

eNauczanie portal
eNauczanie portal is a portal for students to access information.

University Statute
University Statute is a document that outlines the rules and regulations of the university.

Act
Act is a law that outlines the rules and regulations for education.<SEP>The Act refers to the governing laws and regulations overseeing higher education in the region.

Faculty Authorities
Faculty Authorities are responsible for making decisions regarding the curriculum and study plans.

Examination Board
Examination Board is responsible for conducting exams and assessing student performance.

Observer
An observer is a person who monitors the exams and ensures fairness.

Field of Study
Field of study is a specific area of study that a student has chosen.

ECTS Credits
ECTS Credits are a measure of the credits earned by a student.<SEP>ECTS credits are a measure of academic credits earned by students in their field of study.

Study Program
Study Program is a plan of study that outlines the courses and credits required for a degree.

Leave of Absence
Leave of absence is a period of time when a student is not actively attending classes.

Student's University Mail Account
Student's University Mail Account is an email account provided by the university for official communication.

data.entity_name: Individual Student Account in Moja PG System
data.content:
Individual Student Account in Moja PG System
Individual Student Account in Moja PG System is a personalized account for each student to access information and submit applications.

Pregnant Student
Pregnant students have specific rights, such as leaves and continuation of studies.

Parent Student
Parent students have specific rights, such as leaves, to balance family responsibilities with academic commitments.

European Education Framework
The European education framework provides a structure for student exchange and study abroad programs.

Global Education Framework
The global education framework enables students to study abroad and retain student rights at Gdańsk University of Technology.

Study Abroad Program
Study abroad programs allow students to study at other universities while maintaining their student rights.

Curriculum
The curriculum outlines the courses and requirements for a specific field of study.

Disciplinary Proceedings
Disciplinary proceedings are actions taken against students who violate university rules or codes of conduct.

Student Dignity
Student dignity refers to the rights and respect accorded to students within the academic community.
